New Records: Gibraltar's first competitive goal in 713 days, scored by Liam Walker.
Liam Walker now holds the all-time goal record for Gibraltar with six goals.
Key Match Events: Liam Walker scored an Olimpico from the corner flag to give Gibraltar an early lead.
Liam Walker missed a penalty with only eight minutes to go.
Liechtenstein had a goal disallowed for offside in the 92nd minute.
James Scanlon scored Gibraltar's second goal in the 97th minute.
Nicolas Hasler scored a penalty in the 104th minute to equalize for Liechtenstein.
